t for our victories.  It is our responsibility to make things right in this world.  This whole worrying over an apocalypse or heaven ever lasting, is ludicrous to me.  I'd rather not bank on a hope.  I'd rather work on what is here and now, and understanding without knowing why how shaky the ground is beneath my feet.  How precarious life is.  So I don't NOT believe in God, nor do I believe in God...on that whole debate I answer with an affirmative "I have no idea", and leave it at that.  At least I am honest. =) <p><center><B><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117254">Ciffu Longwinded</a></b><br><I>The Token Monkey</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubloodcelt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BloodCelt</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bloodcelt/pics/forum/shocker.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333333>(4/26/02 10:33:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=34>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bloodcelt/pics/forum/ezbc.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: God</span><hr size=1> non-denominational Christian.<br>
